.TH StrListArgs 3 "Last change: 24 August 2005" "Release 0.5" "Ulm's Oberon System"
.SH NAME
StrListArgs \- arguments of type list of strings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Pg
TYPE Member = POINTER TO MemberRec;
TYPE MemberRec =
      RECORD
         string: ConstStrings.String;
         next: Member;
      END;
.sp 0.3
TYPE Value = POINTER TO ValueRec;
TYPE ValueRec =
      RECORD
         (Args.ValueRec)
         head, tail: Member;
      END;
.sp 0.3
VAR type: Args.Type;
.sp 0.7
PROCEDURE Create(VAR value: Args.Value; it: Iterators.Iterator);
.Pe
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I StrListArgs
implements a list of strings argument type for \fIArgs(3)\fP.
Strings are represented as \fIConstStrings.String\fP and chained
through \fIMember\fP nodes. The linear list of strings is represented
by a \fIValue\fP node where \fIhead\fP and \fItail\fP point to
the first and the last member node, respectively.
.PP
.I Create
iterates through all elements accessible through \fIit\fP,
filters out objects that are extensions of \fIConstStrings.String\fP
and inserts them in the given order into the linear list
represented by \fIvalue\fP.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.Tb ConstStrings(3)
.Tp Args(3)
general abstraction for arguments
.Tp ConstStrings(3)
constant strings of arbitrary length
.Te
